# config/ship-ready-denylist.local.txt
#
# Maintainer-specific denylist patterns (NOT shipped — this file is
# gitignored). Copy THIS file (the .example) to `ship-ready-denylist.local.txt`
# and add your private identifiers so the pre-ship grep gate catches
# YOUR leaks before they land in a commit.
#
# Format: one regex per line, grep -E syntax. Lines starting with # are
# harmless unless they contain regex metacharacters.

# Your email prefix (caught in generic code if ever hardcoded)
#your-email@

# Your Windows username subpath (replace 'yourname')
#C:\\Users\\yourname

# Your private project slugs (client repos, experiments, anything that
# shouldn't leak into public templates/standards/prompts)
#project-slug-one
#project-slug-two
#client-internal-project
